Quote: Hundreds of Rotorua people are forming a "carkoi" to travel to Auckland's hikoi on Monday to support calls for Maori seats for the Super City.Auckland iwi have planned the hikoi to demand proper representation in the planned Auckland Super City.Waiariki MP Te Ururoa Flavell, from Rotorua, said he was rapt to hear so many local people were supporting the cause."The people here are professionals when it comes to carkoi and I'm stoked to see that hundreds of them are prepared to take part.
